<topic id='element_general_medical_practice_code__patient_registration_.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: GENERAL MEDICAL PRACTICE CODE (PATIENT REGISTRATION) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_general_medical_practice_code__patient_registration_">GENERAL MEDICAL PRACTICE CODE (PATIENT REGISTRATION)</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
The data for 
              <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_general_medical_practice_code__patient_registration_">GENERAL MEDICAL PRACTICE CODE (PATIENT REGISTRATION)</xref>
 is supplied by the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_prescription_services">NHS Prescription Services</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_general_medical_practice_code__patient_registration_">GENERAL MEDICAL PRACTICE CODE (PATIENT REGISTRATION)</xref>
 is the 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
 of the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_gp_practice">GP Practice</xref>
 that the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is registered with.        </p>
      <p>
         <b>
Use of 
                  <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                  keyref="supporting_definition_organisation_data_service_default_codes">Organisation Data Service Default Codes</xref>
         </b>
      </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <b>V81997</b>
            <p>
should be used when a 
                          <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 presents, who is not currently registered at a 
                          <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_gp_practice">GP Practice</xref>, 
                          <i>but is eligible to be registered should they wish to.</i>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <b>V81998</b>
               <p>
should be used where a 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 should not have a registered 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_gp_practice">GP Practice</xref>.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <b>V81999</b>
               <p>
should be used where it is not possible to determine a 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>'s registered 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_gp_practice">GP Practice</xref>
 code, but it is known that they should have one, or where it is impossible to determine whether they should or shouldn't have a registered practice (for instance the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 cannot communicate and is unidentified).                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
</body>
